  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Their blood have they shed like water round about Jerusalem,.... Without any concern of mind, or remorse of conscience; without any fear of God or man; as if it had been so much water only; and this they shed in great abundance: from the Apocrypha: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "\"And when he had taken all away, he went into his own land, having made a great massacre, and spoken very proudly.'' (1 Maccabees 1:24) ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "\"And spake peaceable words unto them, but all was deceit: for when they had given him credence, he fell suddenly upon the city, and smote it very sore, and destroyed much people of Israel.'' (1 Maccabees 1:30) ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "\"Thus they shed innocent blood on every side of the sanctuary, and defiled it:'' (1 Maccabees 1:37) ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "\"So they rose up against them in battle on the sabbath, and they slew them, with their wives and children and their cattle, to the number of a thousand people.'' (1 Maccabees 2:38) ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "in like manner the blood of the saints has been shed by the antichristian beast of Rome, for which he and his followers will be righteously retaliated, Revelation 17:6. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "in like manner the blood of the saints has been shed by the antichristian beast of Rome, for which he and his followers will be righteously retaliated, ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Revelation 17:6",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ". ",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and there was none to bury them: either the number of the slain was so great, that there were not left enough to bury the dead, or they that did remain were not suffered to do it; this will be the case of the two witnesses, when slain, Revelation 11:7. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "and there was none to bury them: either the number of the slain was so great, that there were not left enough to bury the dead, or they that did remain were not suffered to do it; this will be the case of the two witnesses, when slain, ",
            "children": []
