  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Keil and Delitzsch Biblical Commentary on the Old Testament",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "The Psalm begins with a plaintive description, and in fact one that makes complaint to God. Its opening sounds like ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Lamentations 1:10",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". The defiling does not exclude the reducing to ashes, it is rather spontaneously suggested in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Psalm 74:7",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " in company with wilful incendiarism. The complaint in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Psalm 79:1",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " reminds one of the prophecy of Micah, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Micah 3:12",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", which in its time excited so much vexation (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Jeremiah 26:18",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "); and ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Psalm 79:2",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Deuteronomy 28:26",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". עבדיך confers upon those who were massacred the honour of martyrdom. The lxx renders לעיים by εἰς ὀπωροφυλάκιον, a flourish taken from ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Isaiah 1:8",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". Concerning the quotation from memory in 1 Macc. 7:16f., vid., the introduction to ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Psalm 74",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". The translator of the originally Hebrew First Book of the Maccabees even in other instances betrays an acquaintance with the Greek Psalter (cf. 1 Macc. 1:37, καὶ ἐξέχεαν αἷμα ἀθῷον κύκλῳ τοῦ ἁγιάσματος). \"As water,\" i.e., (cf. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Deuteronomy 15:23",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") without setting any value upon it and without any scruple about it. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Psalm 44:14",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " is repeated in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Psalm 79:4",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". At the time of the Chaldaean catastrophe this applied more particularly to the Edomites. ",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  }
